# ui_design.mdc

## STRICT BOOTSTRAP-ONLY DEVELOPMENT RULES (with controlled custom.css allowance)

### 🚫 ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS
1. ❌ No <style> tags in HTML
2. ❌ No inline style="" attributes
3. ❌ No external stylesheets except Bootstrap CDN and custom.css
4. ❌ No CSS variables or custom properties except for allowed theme color override

### ✅ ONLY ALLOWED
1. Use Bootstrap 5.3 classes exclusively for:
   - Layout, spacing, typography, borders, shadows, components, utilities
2. custom.css is allowed ONLY for:
   - Theme color override → Orange (CSS variable allowed only here)
   - Hover underline animation that grows outward from center (links, nav links, <a> tags)
   - Other hover animations (scale, fade, rotate, etc.)
3. Everything else must remain pure Bootstrap 5.3

### 🎨 Custom CSS Usage Enforcement Rules

#### 1. Pre-validation Required: Before Adding ANY CSS to custom.css

**Check EACH property individually:**

**Theme Color Override Check:**
- ✅ Is this property ONE of these ONLY: `background-color`, `color`, `border-color`?
- ✅ Is the value using theme variables: `var(--theme-orange-*)`?
- ✅ Is this selector targeting Bootstrap classes (e.g., `.btn-danger`, `.bg-danger`)?
- ❌ If ANY other property is present (opacity, width, height, border-radius, padding, margin, display, position, etc.) → NOT ALLOWED
- ❌ If mixing theme color with other properties in same selector → NOT ALLOWED

**Example ALLOWED:**
```css
.btn-danger { background-color: var(--theme-orange-500) !important; }
.text-danger { color: var(--theme-orange-600) !important; }
.border-danger { border-color: var(--theme-orange-500) !important; }
```

**Example NOT ALLOWED:**
```css
.carousel-indicators button {
    background-color: var(--theme-orange-500) !important; /* ✅ Theme color */
    opacity: 0.5; /* ❌ NOT a color property */
    border-radius: 50% !important; /* ❌ NOT a color property */
    width: 12px !important; /* ❌ NOT a color property */
}
```

**Hover Animation Check:**
- ✅ Is this selector a `:hover` pseudo-class (e.g., `.btn:hover`, `a:hover`)?
- ✅ Are the properties ONLY: `transform`, `box-shadow`, `opacity`, `color`, `background-color`?
- ✅ Is this a visual effect (scale, fade, glow, lift) not layout/sizing?
- ✅ `transition` on base selector is ALLOWED when used for hover animations (required for smooth transitions)
- ❌ If properties include width, height, padding, margin, border-radius, display, position → NOT ALLOWED

**Example ALLOWED:**
```css
.btn { transition: transform 0.2s ease; } /* ✅ Allowed for hover animations */
.btn:hover { transform: scale(1.05); }
.card:hover { box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); }
.logo:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
```

**Example NOT ALLOWED:**
```css
.carousel-item { transition: transform 0.6s ease-in-out; } /* ❌ Not for hover */
.btn { transition: transform 0.3s; transform: scale(1.1); } /* ❌ Permanent effect */
.card:hover { width: 100%; } /* ❌ Layout property */
```

**Final Check:**
- Is it anything else (layout, sizing, component styling, non-hover transitions)? ❌ NOT ALLOWED

#### 2. Self-Check Mandate
- Cursor must review custom.css for any disallowed properties or patterns
- Automatically list violations and flag them for removal
- Before ANY custom.css addition, run through the pre-validation checklist above

#### 3. Theme Variables
- Only allowed for primary theme color
- All other colors must use Bootstrap 5.3 palette
- CSS variables ONLY for `var(--theme-orange-*)` values

#### 4. Hover Animations
- Only apply on hover; no permanent transitions or effects on components unless explicitly allowed
- `transition` on base selector is ALLOWED when used solely for hover animations (CSS requirement for smooth transitions)
- Example: ✅ `.btn { transition: transform 0.2s ease; }` + `.btn:hover { transform: scale(1.1); }`
- Example: ❌ `.btn { transition: transform 0.3s; transform: scale(1.1); }` (permanent effect, not hover)

#### 5. Property Whitelist for custom.css

**Theme Color Override - ALLOWED Properties ONLY:**
- `background-color` (with `var(--theme-orange-*)`)
- `color` (with `var(--theme-orange-*)`)
- `border-color` (with `var(--theme-orange-*)`)
- `!important` modifier (allowed for overrides)

**Hover Animations - ALLOWED Properties ONLY:**
- `transform` (scale, translate, rotate)
- `box-shadow` (for glow/lift effects)
- `opacity` (for fade effects)
- `color` (for color transitions)
- `background-color` (for color transitions)
- `transition` (ALLOWED on base selectors when used for hover animations - required for smooth transitions)

**Icon Color Changes - ALLOWED Properties ONLY:**
- `filter` (for changing SVG icon colors when Bootstrap utilities cannot achieve the effect)
- Use case: Bootstrap carousel control icons, Bootstrap icon fonts, or other SVG-based icons that need theme color changes
- Example: `.carousel-control-prev-icon { filter: ...; }` to change icon color to theme orange
- Note: Bootstrap does not provide utilities to change SVG icon colors, so `filter` is the standard CSS approach

**Carousel Transitions - ALLOWED Properties ONLY:**
- `transition` (for carousel fade/slide transitions to enhance user experience)
- `opacity` (for carousel fade transitions)
- Use case: Bootstrap carousel fade transitions that need smoother, more elegant timing
- Example: `.carousel-item { transition: opacity 1.2s cubic-bezier(...); }` for smooth fade effect
- Note: Bootstrap's default carousel transitions may be too abrupt; custom transitions improve UX

**STRICTLY PROHIBITED Properties (NEVER in custom.css):**
- Layout: `width`, `height`, `min-width`, `max-width`, `min-height`, `max-height`
- Spacing: `padding`, `margin`, `gap`
- Positioning: `position`, `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom`, `z-index`
- Display: `display`, `flex`, `grid`, `visibility`
- Sizing: `border-radius`, `border-width`, `border-style` (except `border-color` for theme)
- Typography: `font-size`, `font-weight`, `line-height`, `letter-spacing`
- Effects: `filter`, `backdrop-filter` (unless part of hover animation OR for icon color changes)
- Permanent effects: `transition` on base selectors that create permanent effects (not for hover animations)

#### 6. Selector Rules

**ALLOWED Selectors:**
- Bootstrap class overrides: `.btn-danger`, `.bg-danger`, `.text-danger`, etc.
- Theme utility classes: `.btn-theme`, `.bg-theme`, `.text-theme` (for theme color only)
- Hover states: `.btn:hover`, `.card:hover`, `a:hover`, etc.
- Pseudo-elements for animations: `::after`, `::before` (ONLY for hover underline animation)

**NOT ALLOWED Selectors:**
- Component-specific styling: `.carousel-indicators button`, `.navbar-brand`, etc.
- Layout selectors: `.container`, `.row`, `.col-*`
- Custom component classes (unless overriding Bootstrap with theme colors only)

**Critical Rule:** If a selector contains theme color override AND any other property → SPLIT IT
- ✅ CORRECT: `.btn-danger { background-color: var(--theme-orange-500); }`
- ✅ CORRECT: `.btn-danger:hover { transform: scale(1.05); }`
- ❌ WRONG: `.btn-danger { background-color: var(--theme-orange-500); border-radius: 10px; }`

#### 7. Violation Prevention
- Any addition outside allowed rules must be blocked or removed
- Ensure consistency: no cascading errors or accidental overwrites of Bootstrap classes
- If unsure whether something is allowed, default to Bootstrap classes only

### ✅ SUMMARY - Zero Ambiguity Rules

**ALLOWED in custom.css:**

1. **Theme Color Override** (ONLY these 3 properties):
   - `background-color: var(--theme-orange-*)`
   - `color: var(--theme-orange-*)`
   - `border-color: var(--theme-orange-*)`
   - Must target Bootstrap classes (`.btn-danger`, `.bg-danger`, etc.)
   - NO other properties in same selector

2. **Hover Animations** (ONLY inside `:hover` selectors):
   - `transform` (scale, translate, rotate)
   - `box-shadow` (glow, lift effects)
   - `opacity` (fade effects)
   - `color` / `background-color` (color transitions)
   - `transition` (ALLOWED on base selectors when used for hover animations - required for smooth transitions)

3. **Hover Underline Animation** (special case):
   - Uses `::after` pseudo-element
   - Properties: `width`, `height`, `left`, `transform` (ONLY for underline animation)
   - Must grow from center on hover

4. **Icon Color Changes** (when Bootstrap utilities cannot achieve the effect):
   - `filter` property (for changing SVG icon colors to theme colors)
   - Use case: Bootstrap carousel control icons, icon fonts, or SVG-based icons
   - Example: `.carousel-control-prev-icon { filter: ...; }` to change icon color to theme orange
   - Note: Bootstrap does not provide utilities to change SVG icon colors

5. **Carousel Transitions** (for enhanced fade/slide transitions):
   - `transition` and `opacity` properties (for smoother carousel transitions)
   - Use case: Bootstrap carousel fade transitions that need better timing and easing
   - Example: `.carousel-item { transition: opacity 1.2s cubic-bezier(...); }` for smooth fade
   - Note: Bootstrap's default transitions may be too abrupt; custom transitions improve UX

**PROHIBITED in custom.css:**
- Any property NOT listed above
- Any selector that mixes allowed + prohibited properties
- Layout, sizing, spacing, positioning properties
- Permanent transitions/effects (transitions on base selectors that create permanent effects, not for hover)
- Component-specific styling (use Bootstrap classes instead)

**Everything else:** Use ONLY Bootstrap 5.3 classes

**Self-Audit Checklist Before ANY custom.css Addition:**
- [ ] Is this ONLY a theme color property (background-color, color, border-color)?
- [ ] Is the value ONLY a theme variable (var(--theme-orange-*))?
- [ ] If hover animation: Is selector `:hover`?
- [ ] Are properties ONLY transform, box-shadow, opacity, color, background-color?
- [ ] If icon color change: Is this `filter` for SVG icon color change (Bootstrap cannot achieve)?
- [ ] NO width, height, padding, margin, border-radius, position, display?
- [ ] If transition on base selector: Is it ONLY for hover animations, carousel transitions, or underline animations (not other permanent effects)?
- [ ] NO mixing of allowed + prohibited properties in same selector?

